episodes.title: Perfect
episodes.plot: Bluey wants to draw the perfect Father's Day card by remembering fun games she's played with Dad, but starts to get frustrated when she finds a problem with each drawing. None of them are perfect enough.

episodes.title: Bedroom
episodes.plot: Bluey is excited to get her own room. But when bed time comes, she misses Bingo more than she expected and must find a way to stay in touch with her sister.

episodes.title: Obstacle Course
episodes.plot: Mum sets up a backyard obstacle course just for fun, but Dad wants to race. Now the kids are determined to win by any means necessary.

episodes.title: Promises
episodes.plot: Bluey keeps breaking her promises. But after seeing how much Bingo trusts Mum's word, Bluey learns the power of promises and why it's important not to break them.

episodes.title: Omelette
episodes.plot: Bingo is helping Mum make an omelette for Dad's birthday breakfast, but cracking eggs is harder than it looks and Dad is getting hungrier by the minute.

episodes.title: Born Yesterday
episodes.plot: When Dad pretends he was born yesterday, Bluey and Bingo have to guide him through his second day on Earth, especially when he discovers food is delicious and steals Lucky Dad's pie.

episodes.title: Mini Bluey
episodes.plot: When Dad complains about how dissimilar Bluey and Bingo are, Bluey hatches a plan to make them more alike and happily introduces Mini-Bluey.

episodes.title: Unicorse
episodes.plot: Bluey can't get to sleep, so Mum reads her one last story. But they are interrupted by Unicorse, the most annoying hand puppet in the world, who Bluey tries to reform.

episodes.title: Curry Quest
episodes.plot: Bingo and Dad must brave a swooping magpie protecting its nest when they go on a curry swap to Mackenzie's house through the park.

episodes.title: Magic
episodes.plot: Bluey teaches Bingo how to use magic so she can make Mum play with her, but she forgets to explain the most important rule - never use magic for cheekiness.

episodes.title: Chest
episodes.plot: Dad tries to teach Bluey how to play chess, but Mum thinks she is still too young. When Bingo joins in, the kids make up their own rules, but they still can't beat Dad.

episodes.title: Sheep Dog
episodes.plot: Dad agrees to play Sheepdog with Bluey and Bingo to stop them from disturbing Mum who is taking a well-earned rest. But looking after a sheep is harder work than they expected.

episodes.title: Housework
episodes.plot: Mum and Dad vow to only finish their boring housework when the kids stop acting silly, but that's never going to happen, so they end up trying the same approach themselves.

episodes.title: Pass The Parcel
episodes.plot: Lucky's Dad is outraged that modern Pass the Parcel has a present in every layer and changes the rules back to only having one prize in the middle, but Bingo is forever losing.

episodes.title: Explorers
episodes.plot: While waiting to be picked up from school, Jack plays at being a sailor trying to find his way back home to Australia. Meanwhile, Jack's Dad has got lost en route to collect him.

episodes.title: Phones
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo want to play restaurants with Grandad, but it's a little different than he's used to - he's going to need an app to order the food.

episodes.title: Pavlova
episodes.plot: Mum won't let Bingo have Pavlova, so the kids find a way by playing a cheeky game of Cafe in the kitchen. But Dad the chef sets up a competing shop that only serves edamame beans.

episodes.title: Rain
episodes.plot: When a heavy summer rain thunders over the Heeler home, Bluey is determined to dam the water in the front yard, while Mum tries to stop her constantly tracking mud into the house.

episodes.title: Pizza Girls
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo are making mud pizzas and delivering them to the grownups, but their pedal car's wheel keeps falling off.

episodes.title: Driving
episodes.plot: With only five minutes to play 'Driving', Bluey and Mum race against the clock to buy milk for a grumpy guest and have to escape an angry shopkeeper.

episodes.title: Tina
episodes.plot: Tired of being told what to do, Bluey and Bingo enlist their giant invisible friend to show Mum and Dad who's boss. Now they can do anything they want, until Mum and Dad rebel.

episodes.title: Whale Watching
episodes.plot: Bluey promises her customer Bingo 'the best tour ever' in a game of Whale Watching, but they need Mum and Dad to join in and they are too tired to play after a late night.

episodes.title: Family Meeting
episodes.plot: When Dad's accused of 'fluffing' in Bluey's face as he climbed out of bed, he's put on trial with Mum as the judge and Bluey and Bingo as witnesses. But what was Bluey doing there?

episodes.title: Faceytalk
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo love to video chat with Muffin and Socks so they can all draw pictures together. When Muffin won't give Socks a turn, the kids discover what happens when you hog.

episodes.title: Ragdoll
episodes.plot: Dad agrees to take Bluey and Bingo to the shops to buy an ice-cream if they can get him into the car. Only problem is - he's just entered 'Ragdoll' mode.

episodes.title: Fairytale
episodes.plot: Dad tells Bluey and Bingo a real-life fairy tale about growing up in a wild place called the 80s, about a boy who was cursed when he was mean to his little brother.

episodes.title: Musical Statues
episodes.plot: At the end of a long day, Bluey and her family are out of sync and out of sorts, so Mum gets everyone to play musical statues.

episodes.title: Stories
episodes.plot: Indy thinks she's no good because her model horse looks like a cow, but Calypso encourages her not to give up, so she tries to fix it with a little help from Winton.

episodes.title: Puppets
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo teach Unicorse good manners so he can ask Mum on a date, but things go awry when Unicorse eats a tick.

episodes.title: Turtleboy
episodes.plot: Bingo finds a toy turtle at the playground and wants to take him home, but Dad says it's not the done thing.

episodes.title: Onesies
episodes.plot: When Mum's sister Brandy comes over for a visit, she brings the kids onesies as a present, which has an unexpected effect on Bingo.

episodes.title: Tradies
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo hide under the house and spy on two mysterious tradies working in the backyard.

episodes.title: Granny Mobile
episodes.plot: Muffin is playing Grouchy Granny at a garage sale, making Dad push her on an old mobility scooter. But when a real Grouchy Granny wants to buy it, Muffin won't budge.

episodes.title: Space
episodes.plot: Mackenzie, Jack and Rusty are playing as astronauts on a mission to Mars. But during their journey, Mackenzie keeps going missing and no one knows why, not even Mackenzie.

episodes.title: Smoochy Kiss
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo want Dad all to themselves until they discover he has some gross habits.

episodes.title: Dirt
episodes.plot: Judo wants to play in the dirt with Bluey and Bingo, but she's not supposed to get dirty.

episodes.title: The Decider
episodes.plot: The Heelers and Lucky's family get together to watch the big game.

episodes.title: Cubby
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo build a very special cubby for their stuffed toy Kimjim.

episodes.title: Exercise
episodes.plot: Bingo pretends to be Boss Bluey's new employee in the middle of Dad's backyard workout.

episodes.title: Relax
episodes.plot: Bluey and Bingo would rather explore their holiday hotel room than relax on the beach.

episodes.title: Stickbird
episodes.plot: On a trip to the beach, Mum teaches Bluey to throw, while Bingo and Dad get creative with a funny shaped stick.

episodes.title: Show and Tell
episodes.plot: Bluey wants to know why Dad's always bossing her around.

episodes.title: Dragon
episodes.plot: Bluey asks Dad to help her draw a dragon for her story.

episodes.title: Wild Girls
episodes.plot: Coco wants to play Wild Girls with Indy, but Chloe wants her to play another game.

episodes.title: TV Shop
episodes.plot: At the chemist, Bluey and Bingo have fun playing with the CCTV screens.

episodes.title: Slide
episodes.plot: Bingo and Lila are excited to play on their new waterslide.

episodes.title: Cricket
episodes.plot: During a friendly game of neighbourhood cricket, the dads struggle to bowl Rusty out.
